20/12/2009
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The prosecution announced on Friday (December 18th) they have arrested a former Bosnian Serb police officer suspected of genocide committed in the 1995 Srebrenica massacre. Goran Markovic, 46, was detained in the town of Bijeljina in the country's northeast early on Friday, the prosecution said. He is suspected of having committed the crime in his capacity as commander of a police unit. (AP, Sarajevo-x, Dnevni Avaz - 18/12/09)
